WorkItem.Description:
As of Revision 18247, the example svg document given at http://www.w3.org/TR/SVG/paths.html#PathDataEllipticalArcCommands fails to render correctly.
The offending code in Paths\SvgArcSegment.cs is:
102:	root = (this.Size == SvgArcSize.Large && this.Sweep == SvgArcSweep.Positive ? -1.0 : 1.0) * Math.Sqrt(numerator / (this.RadiusX * this.RadiusX * y1dash * y1dash + this.RadiusY * this.RadiusY * x1dash * x1dash));
It should be:
102:	root = ((this.Size == SvgArcSize.Large && this.Sweep == SvgArcSweep.Positive) || (this.Size == SvgArcSize.Small && this.Sweep == SvgArcSweep.Negative) ? -1.0 : 1.0) * Math.Sqrt(numerator / (this.RadiusX * this.RadiusX * y1dash * y1dash + this.RadiusY * this.RadiusY * x1dash * x1dash));
The specs say that the negative root be taken if large-arc-flag == sweep-flag.
Â 
Also, for better adherence to the SVG 1.1 spec, the lines in Paths\SvgPathBuilder.cs:
60:	size = (coords[i + 3] == 1.0f) ? SvgArcSize.Large : SvgArcSize.Small;
61:	sweep = (coords[i + 4] == 1.0f) ? SvgArcSweep.Positive : SvgArcSweep.Negative;
Could be changed to
60:	size = (coords[i + 3] != 0.0f) ? SvgArcSize.Large : SvgArcSize.Small;
61:	sweep = (coords[i + 4] != 0.0f) ? SvgArcSweep.Positive : SvgArcSweep.Negative;
The specs say that non-zero values for the large-arc-flag and sweep-flag should be treated as being a 1.
